47
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:31,800
All right.
好的。

48
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:35,280
Well, we're going to hear both of these words in the dialogue.
嗯，我们会在对话中听到这两个词。

49
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:40,960
So why don't we listen as Gary visits his dentist?
那么，我们不如听听Gary去看牙医时的对话吧？

50
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:54,760
Hey, Gary, great to see you again.
嘿，Gary，很高兴再次见到你。

51
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:57,720
Please have a seat.
请坐。

52
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:02,160
So tell me what seems to be the problem.
告诉我哪里不舒服。

53
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:03,560
Thanks, doc.
谢谢，医生。

54
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,320
I've got a really bad toothache.
我牙痛得厉害。

55
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,320
I can't eat anything.
我什么都吃不了。

56
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,880
And look, my face is all swollen.
你看，我的脸都肿了。

57
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,680
I think it might be my wisdom teeth.
我想可能是我的智齿出了问题。

58
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:16,880
Well, let's have a look.
嗯，让我看看。

59
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:21,880
Open wide.
张大嘴。

60
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:29,880
This doesn't look good.
情况看起来不太好。

61
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:36,360
Well, it looks like you have a cavity and your crown is loose.
嗯，看起来你有个蛀牙，而且牙冠松了。

62
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,360
You'll need to put in a filling before it gets any worse.
你需要补牙，以免情况恶化。

63
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:44,520
And the crown probably needs to be refitted.
牙冠可能需要重新安装。

64
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:49,000
I'm going to order some x-rays.
我要给你拍几张X光片。

65
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Is it going to hurt?
会疼吗？

66
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,920
No, not at all.
不，一点也不疼。

67
00:02:53,920 --> 00:03:00,920
Just lay back and relax.
躺下放松就好。

68
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:07,920
Okay, spit.
好了，吐出来。

69
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:19,520
Okay, that always happens.
好吧，这种事总是发生。

70
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,560
The dentist says, no, it's not going to hurt.
牙医说：“不，不会疼的。”

71
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,560
Don't worry about it.
“别担心。”

72
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:25,440
But it always hurts much more than he says.
但实际上总是比他说的疼得多。

73
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,440
Exactly.
没错。

74
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:31,480
So in this dialogue, we saw some interesting words when the dentist was describing what
所以在这个对话中，我们看到了一些有趣的词，是牙医在描述

75
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,000
problems Gary had.
Gary的问题时用的。

76
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Yes.
是的。

77
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,560
So why don't we look at those now in Language Takeaway.
那么，我们不如在“语言要点”环节中看看这些词。

78
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,560
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

79
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:43,080
All right, let's take a look at our first word.
好的，让我们看看第一个词。

80
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:47,440
So Gary said that his face was all swollen.
Gary说他的脸都肿了。

81
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,440
Swollen.
肿的。

82
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,440
Swollen.
肿的。

83
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:50,440
Swollen.
肿的。

84
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:54,760
So swollen is an adjective, right Marco?
所以“swollen”是形容词，对吧，Marco？

85
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:55,760
Right.
对。

86
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:59,560
So his face is or was swollen.
所以他的脸是肿的。

87
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,560
It was bigger.
它变大了。

88
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,920
Yeah, his face was bigger than normal.
是的，他的脸比正常情况大。

89
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,920
Yes.
是的。

90
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:07,400
Often when you hurt yourself, that part of your body becomes swollen.
通常当你受伤时，身体的那个部位会肿起来。

91
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,400
Swollen, right.
肿的，对。

92
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:12,880
So you have to put some ice on it usually and then the swelling will go down.
所以通常你要敷点冰，然后肿胀就会消退。

93
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,080
And that's the noun, the swelling.
那是名词“swelling”（肿胀）。

94
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,440
Right, the swelling.
对，肿胀。

95
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:18,480
And well, the verb to swell.
嗯，动词是“to swell”（肿胀）。

96
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:21,400
All right, three words for the price of one.
好的，一个词三种形式。

97
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:28,880
So let's listen to some examples of how we would use the swelling, swollen and to swell.
那么让我们听一些例子，看看如何使用“swelling”、“swollen”和“to swell”。

98
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:31,400
Example one.
例子一。

99
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,840
My nose is swollen.
我的鼻子肿了。

100
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:37,000
It's the size of a football.
它像个足球那么大。

101
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Example two.
例子二。

102
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:44,920
Put some ice on your foot and the swelling will go down.
在你的脚上敷些冰，肿胀就会消退。

103
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:47,200
Example three.
例子三。

104
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:52,600
I got bitten by a spider and my hand is swelling up.
我被蜘蛛咬了，手正在肿起来。

105
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:58,720
All right, so Gary's face was swollen and he thought that it was his wisdom teeth.
好的，所以Gary的脸肿了，他认为是他的智齿出了问题。

106
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,880
Wisdom teeth.
智齿。

107
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,880
Wisdom teeth.
智齿。

108
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,440
Okay, so this is interesting.
好的，这很有趣。

109
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,440
Wisdom is like wise.
“Wisdom”是“wise”（智慧）的意思。

110
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,440
Yeah, knowledge.
是的，知识。

111
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,440
Knowledge.
知识。

112
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,440
Yeah.
是的。

113
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:10,080
So these teeth, they're not knowledgeable, but they're called wisdom teeth.
所以这些牙齿，它们并不有知识，但被称为智齿。

114
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,480
They're the teeth that grow last in your mouth, right?
它们是嘴里最后长出来的牙齿，对吧？

115
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:16,560
Right, they are the last teeth at the very end of your mouth.
对，它们是嘴巴最里面的最后几颗牙。

116
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:20,440
Yes, and usually you get them when you're about 20.
是的，通常你在20岁左右长出来。

117
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:26,000
And since they come out at this age, sometimes they interfere or they hurt a little bit,
而且因为它们在这个年龄长出来，有时会干扰或有点疼，

118
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,920
so you have to get them taken out.
所以你可能需要拔掉它们。

119
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,920
Yes.
是的。

120
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,680
All right, wisdom teeth.
好的，智齿。

121
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:31,680
Wisdom teeth.
智齿。

122
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:36,200
Okay, now for our next word and something that we all got as children.
好的，现在看下一个词，我们小时候都经历过的东西。

123
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,200
Cavity.
蛀牙。

124
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,200
Cavity.
蛀牙。

125
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,200
A cavity.
一个蛀牙。

126
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,200
A cavity.
一个蛀牙。

127
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,200
It's a hole in your tooth.
就是牙齿上的一个洞。

128
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,200
A hole in your tooth.
牙齿上的一个洞。

129
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,040
And it's caused by?
它是由什么引起的？

130
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,040
Too much sugar.
吃太多糖。

131
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,040
Too much sugar, right?
吃太多糖，对吧？

132
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,760
Or not brushing your teeth enough.
或者刷牙不够。

133
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:48,760
Yeah.
是的。

134
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:51,440
So that's why everyone had it, I think, as children.
所以我想每个人小时候都得过。

135
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,440
Cavities.
蛀牙。

136
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,440
I never had a cavity.
我从来没有蛀牙。

137
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,440
Really?
真的吗？

138
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,440
Yeah.
是的。

139
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,440
Wow, didn't have much sugar?
哇，没吃太多糖？

140
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,200
I guess I was a bit of a health nut when I was a kid.
我想我小时候算是个健康狂人。

141
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,200
Well, no, I wasn't.
嗯，不，我不是。

142
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,200
My mom was.
是我妈妈是。

143
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,680
No, I guess not.
不，我想不是。

144
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:05,200
All right, but enough about my eating habits.
好了，关于我的饮食习惯就聊到这里。

145
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,640
Let's talk about our next word, crown.
让我们谈谈下一个词，“crown”（牙冠）。

146
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,640
Crown.
牙冠。

147
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,520
A crown.
一个牙冠。

148
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:13,240
So a crown, this is interesting.
所以“crown”，这很有趣。

149
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,120
We're not talking kings and queens.
我们不是在说国王和王后。

150
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,320
That's the first thing that comes to mind, right?
那是首先想到的，对吧？

151
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,800
No, a crown is actually the visible part of your teeth.
不，牙冠实际上是你牙齿的可见部分。

152
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:25,200
Okay, so there's one part of your tooth that's inside that you can't see, right?
好的，所以牙齿有一部分在里面你看不到，对吧？

153
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,200
That's called the root.
那叫牙根。

154
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,200
Yes.
是的。

155
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:32,220
So when he said your crown is loose, was he talking really about the actual tooth?
所以当他说“你的牙冠松了”时，他真的是在说牙齿本身吗？

156
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:36,540
So sometimes people will lose a tooth or have a really bad cavity.
所以有时人们会掉牙或蛀牙很严重。

157
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:42,000
So the dentist needs to make a new crown or a new visible part of the tooth for you.
那么牙医需要为你做一个新的牙冠，也就是牙齿新的可见部分。

158
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,920
So sometimes it'll be made of gold.
有时它会用金子做。

159
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,920
Yep.
对。

160
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,920
Or porcelain.
或者瓷器。

161
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,920
Porcelain, exactly.
瓷器，没错。

162
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:51,760
So a crown, it's like a really, really, really big filling.
所以牙冠就像一个非常非常大的补牙材料。

163
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,480
A crown.
牙冠。

164
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,360
So his crown needed to be refitted or put back into place.
所以他的牙冠需要重新安装或复位。

165
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,360
Yes.
是的。

166
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,280
Now our final word, filling.
现在最后一个词，“filling”（补牙材料）。

167
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,280
Filling.
补牙材料。

168
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,280
A filling.
一个补牙材料。

169
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,280
A filling.
一个补牙材料。

170
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:06,200
So I just said this word previously.
我刚才说过这个词。

171
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:10,000
Now when you have a cavity, you need to fill it in.
当你有蛀牙时，你需要把它填上。

172
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,960
Right, you need to fill it with something.
对，你需要用东西填满它。

173
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,960
Yes.
是的。

174
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,720
It's usually some sort of paste.
通常是一些糊状物。

175
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:17,320
And it gets really hard, just like your tooth.
然后它会变得很硬，就像你的牙齿一样。

176
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,320
Exactly.
没错。

177
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:20,080
So then it covers up this cavity.
这样它就能盖住这个蛀洞。

178
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,080
Filling.
补牙材料。

179
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,080
A filling.
一个补牙材料。

180
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,080
I have many fillings.
我有很多补牙材料。

181
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,480
I wasn't very healthy as a kid.
我小时候不太健康。

182
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,400
All right, not a good toothbrusher.
好吧，不是个好刷牙的人。

183
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,400
Exactly.
没错。

184
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:32,400
So why don't we listen to this dialogue again, and then we'll come back and talk a little
那么，我们不如再听一遍这个对话，然后回来聊聊

185
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:36,880
bit about some of the interesting phrases that the doctor used.
医生用的一些有趣的短语。

186
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:42,440
Hey, Gary.
